bioghist.p:
Wayne Smith is the author of several books including 
                            Castro's Cuba: Soviet Partner or Nonaligned? (1985); 
                            The Closest of Enemies: Personal and Diplomatic Account of United States-Cuban Relations Since 1957 (1988); 
                            Subject to Solution: Problems in Cuban-U.S. Relations (1988); 
                            Portrait of Cuba (1991); and 
                            The Russians Aren't Coming: New Soviet Policy in Latin America (1992). In addition to being interviewed for the Fidel film, Smith appears in many of Estela Bravo's other documentaries.
